<i>Now, write this down, write this down.</i>
<i>Exactly what happened.</i>

01:13:35.010 --> 01:13:37.490
<i>I'm gonna write down what happened.</i>
<i>Come on, come on! I've got to find a pen!</i>

01:13:37.730 --> 01:13:40.450
<i>Jeez! Come on! Come on, keep focused.</i>

01:13:40.690 --> 01:13:41.770
<i>Keep focused.</i>

01:13:42.010 --> 01:13:45.010
<i>Keep... Keep it in mind.</i>
<i>Come on, find a pen.</i>

01:13:45.250 --> 01:13:47.530
<i>Write this note.</i>
<i>Write down what happened. Write it down.</i>

01:13:47.770 --> 01:13:51.530
<i>Come on, concentrate.</i>
<i>Keep it in mind. Find a p...</i>

01:13:58.330 --> 01:13:59.250
What happened?

01:13:59.490 --> 01:14:01.290
What does it look like?
He beat the shit out of me.

01:14:01.530 --> 01:14:03.330
- Who?
- Who?

01:14:03.570 --> 01:14:08.290
Fuck, Leonard, Dodd!
Dodd beat the shit out of me.

01:14:15.130 --> 01:14:18.610
- Hello?

01:14:20.330 --> 01:14:24.010
It's Burt, from the front desk.

01:14:24.090 --> 01:14:25.290
Yeah?

01:14:25.530 --> 01:14:29.490
I know you said you didn't want any calls
but this guy on the phone says he's a cop.

01:14:29.730 --> 01:14:31.570
- A cop?
- Yeah.

01:14:31.810 --> 01:14:34.770
He says you're really gonna wanna know
what he has to say.

01:14:35.010 --> 01:14:38.010
I'm not too good on the phone.
I need to look people in the eye.

01:14:38.250 --> 01:14:41.530
Well, what...

01:14:43.410 --> 01:14:46.170
You can, um, you can crash on the couch.

01:14:46.410 --> 01:14:49.010
It's comfortable. Just have a seat.

01:14:49.250 --> 01:14:52.530
Thanks.

01:14:55.690 --> 01:14:58.250
So, how long do you think it's gonna take you?

01:14:58.490 --> 01:14:59.290
Hm?

01:14:59.530 --> 01:15:03.170
You told me you were looking
for the guy who killed your wife.

01:15:03.410 --> 01:15:10.530
Oh, it depends on if he's here in town
or if he's moved on. I have my file here.

01:15:10.810 --> 01:15:12.610
Can I ask you something?

01:15:12.850 --> 01:15:18.130
If you have all that information,
why haven't the police found him for you?

01:15:18.370 --> 01:15:21.170
- They're not looking for him.
- Why not?

01:15:21.410 --> 01:15:23.930
They don't think he exists.

01:15:24.170 --> 01:15:31.450
You see, I told them what I remembered.
I was asleep. Something woke me up.

01:15:35.410 --> 01:15:40.490
Her side of the bed was cold.
She'd obviously been gone for a while.

01:16:34.850 --> 01:16:37.250
There had to be a second man.

01:16:37.490 --> 01:16:39.690
Somebody hit me from behind.
I remember.

01:16:39.930 --> 01:16:41.370
It's the last thing I do remember.

01:16:41.610 --> 01:16:44.050
Look, the police didn't believe me.
If we check...

01:16:44.290 --> 01:16:49.490
How did they explain what you do remember? 
The gun and stuff?

01:16:50.690 --> 01:16:52.730
John G was clever.

01:16:52.970 --> 01:16:54.570
He was clever.

01:16:54.810 --> 01:16:59.410
He took the dead man's gun 
and replaced it with the sap he hit me with.

01:16:59.650 --> 01:17:03.450
He left my gun and the getaway car.
He gave the police a complete package.

01:17:03.690 --> 01:17:08.050
They found the sap with my blood on it
in the dead man's hand.

01:17:08.290 --> 01:17:10.450
And they only found my gun.

01:17:10.690 --> 01:17:13.490
They didn't need to look for anybody else.

01:17:13.730 --> 01:17:17.450
I was the only guy who disagreed
with the facts and I had brain damage.

01:17:17.690 --> 01:17:20.490
The cops are not gonna believe someone in my condition.

01:17:20.730 --> 01:17:25.130
Leonard. You can stay here for a couple of days 
if it will help you.

01:17:25.370 --> 01:17:27.250
Oh, thanks.

01:17:27.490 --> 01:17:31.690
I have to go back to work,
so, um, just make yourself at home.

01:17:31.930 --> 01:17:34.130
You can watch TV or have some food.

01:17:34.370 --> 01:17:36.650
Whatever you want, OK?
Make yourself at home.

01:17:36.890 --> 01:17:39.890
One thing.

01:17:41.530 --> 01:17:47.250
- Something to remember you by.
- My name is Natalie.

01:17:47.490 --> 01:17:50.970
Natalie.

01:18:20.130 --> 01:18:22.090
- What's wrong?
- Somebody's come already.

01:19:09.370 --> 01:19:13.850
- On the house.
- Thanks.

01:19:16.490 --> 01:19:20.090
My, you really do have a problem.
Just like that cop said.

01:19:20.330 --> 01:19:24.090
- Hm?
- Your condition.

01:19:24.330 --> 01:19:27.010
Well, nobody's perfect.

01:19:27.250 --> 01:19:32.330
What's the last thing that you do remember?

01:19:33.810 --> 01:19:35.690
- My wife.
- That's sweet.

01:19:35.930 --> 01:19:38.290
Dying.

01:19:38.610 --> 01:19:42.490
I remember my wife dying.

01:19:44.490 --> 01:19:47.090
Let me, um, get you another one.

01:19:47.330 --> 01:19:50.730
I think this one's dusty.

01:19:53.290 --> 01:19:55.930
Why are you calling me?
What do you want?

01:19:56.170 --> 01:19:59.570
I know you're a cop. What do you want?
Have I done something wrong?

01:19:59.810 --> 01:20:03.290
I don't know, something bad, maybe.

01:20:03.530 --> 01:20:05.730
Look, why are you asking me?
I can't remember what I've done.

01:20:05.970 --> 01:20:07.770
You wouldn't believe me anyway.

01:20:08.010 --> 01:20:10.690
Because of my condition, 
you don't believe someone with this condition.

01:20:10.930 --> 01:20:14.090
Nobody believed Sammy!
I didn't even fucking believe Sammy!

01:20:14.330 --> 01:20:17.810
<i>Ferdy's bar.</i>

01:20:18.370 --> 01:20:22.290
<i>Come by after. Natalie.</i>

01:20:35.090 --> 01:20:36.810
- A beer, please.
- What do you want?

01:20:37.050 --> 01:20:37.850
A beer, please.

01:20:38.090 --> 01:20:40.250
You can't just waltz in here dressed like that 
and ask for a beer.

01:20:40.490 --> 01:20:42.570
- What, is there a dress code?
- Why are you here?

01:20:42.810 --> 01:20:45.490
- I'm meeting someone called Natalie.
- Well, that's me.

01:20:45.730 --> 01:20:48.930
Yeah, we met before, right?

01:20:49.170 --> 01:20:51.170
- Then why am I here?
- I don't know, why don't you tell me?

01:20:51.410 --> 01:20:53.210
I don't remember.
I have no short-term memory.

01:20:53.450 --> 01:20:55.010
Oh, you're that memory guy.

01:20:55.250 --> 01:20:58.690
- How do you know about me?
- My boyfriend told me about you.

01:20:58.930 --> 01:21:03.610
- Oh, yeah? Who's your boyfriend?
- Jimmy Grants. Do you know him?

01:21:03.850 --> 01:21:05.050
No.

01:21:05.290 --> 01:21:10.250
He knows you. He told me about you.
He said you were staying at the Discount.

01:21:10.490 --> 01:21:13.490
In fact, a cop came by earlier
and was looking for you.

01:21:13.730 --> 01:21:15.610
Said he was looking for a guy
who can't remember anything...

01:21:15.850 --> 01:21:17.650
wouldn't know how he'd got here
or what he'd done.

01:21:17.890 --> 01:21:19.570
I get a lot of guys round here like that.

01:21:19.810 --> 01:21:25.610
Chronic alcoholism
is one cause of short-term memory loss.

01:21:25.730 --> 01:21:28.530
- Are you Teddy?
- No, my name's Leonard.

01:21:28.770 --> 01:21:31.170
- Did Teddy send you?
- I don't know.

01:21:31.410 --> 01:21:33.210
What's happened to Jimmy?

01:21:33.450 --> 01:21:36.850
- I don't know that, either. Sorry.
- You don't remember anything?

01:21:37.090 --> 01:21:40.370
You don't remember where you've been
or what you've just done?

01:21:40.610 --> 01:21:43.850
I can't make new memories.
Everything just fades.

01:21:44.090 --> 01:21:48.250
- Then why did you come here?
- I found this in my pocket.

01:21:49.890 --> 01:21:53.450
Your pocket?

01:22:15.290 --> 01:22:17.850
Bar bet. Care to contribute?

01:22:18.090 --> 01:22:20.570
- No, thanks.
- It's for a lot of money.

01:22:20.810 --> 01:22:26.090
Come on. Proceeds are going to charity.
Help me out.

01:22:35.490 --> 01:22:38.730
Thank you.

01:22:53.450 --> 01:22:56.570
- On the house.
- Thanks.

01:23:00.170 --> 01:23:03.250
It's completely fucked because nobody believes you.

01:23:03.490 --> 01:23:06.890
It's amazing what a little brain damage
will do for your credibility.

01:23:07.130 --> 01:23:09.210
I guess it's poetic justice
for not believing Sammy.

01:23:09.450 --> 01:23:13.890
You know the truth about my condition, officer? 
You don't know anything.

01:23:14.130 --> 01:23:18.850
You feel angry, you don't know why.
You feel guilty, you have no idea why.

01:23:19.090 --> 01:23:22.290
You could do anything 
and not have the faintest idea ten minutes later.

01:23:22.530 --> 01:23:25.250
Like Sammy.
What if I'd done something like Sammy?

01:23:25.490 --> 01:23:29.090
I didn't tell you?
What happened to Sammy and his wife?

01:23:29.330 --> 01:23:31.250
She came to see me at my office.

01:23:31.490 --> 01:23:36.050
<i>I didn't tell her what I really thought</i>
<i>but I never said that he was faking.</i>

01:23:36.290 --> 01:23:38.250
<i>Just that his condition was mental,</i>
<i>not physical.</i>

01:23:38.490 --> 01:23:42.530
<i>I found out later that she went home</i>
<i>and gave Sammy his final exam.</i>

01:23:42.770 --> 01:23:47.010
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

01:24:00.850 --> 01:24:03.650
<i>She knew beyond a doubt that he loved her,</i>

01:24:03.890 --> 01:24:08.010
<i>so she found a way to test him.</i>

01:24:17.970 --> 01:24:22.090
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

01:24:22.330 --> 01:24:25.810
Hm.

01:24:31.290 --> 01:24:34.730
<i>- She really thought she'd call his bluff.</i>
- There you go.

01:24:34.970 --> 01:24:41.010
<i>Or she just didn't want to live with the things</i>
<i>she'd put him through.</i>

01:24:47.850 --> 01:24:50.730
Sammy?

01:24:51.290 --> 01:24:54.170
It's time for my shot.

01:24:58.570 --> 01:25:01.810
It won't hurt.

01:25:42.330 --> 01:25:45.330
<i>She went into a coma and never recovered.</i>

01:25:45.570 --> 01:25:48.530
<i>Sammy couldn't understand</i>
<i>or explain what happened.</i>

01:25:48.770 --> 01:25:50.570
Oh!

01:25:50.810 --> 01:25:54.930
He's been in a home ever since.
He doesn't even know his wife is dead.

01:25:55.170 --> 01:25:58.250
I was wrong about Sammy
and I was wrong about his wife.

01:25:58.490 --> 01:26:02.330
She wasn't interested in the money.
She needed to understand his problem.

01:26:02.570 --> 01:26:05.970
<i>His brain didn't respond to conditioning</i>
<i>but he wasn't a con man.</i>

01:26:06.210 --> 01:26:09.330
<i>And when she looked into his eyes,</i>
<i>she thought he could be the same person.</i>

01:26:09.570 --> 01:26:11.410
<i>When I looked into his eyes,</i>
<i>I thought I saw recognition.</i>

01:26:11.650 --> 01:26:13.450
Now I know you fake it.

01:26:13.690 --> 01:26:16.490
If you think you're supposed to recognise somebody, 
you pretend to.

01:26:16.730 --> 01:26:20.010
<i>You bluff it to get a pat on the head</i>
<i>from the doctors.</i>

01:26:20.250 --> 01:26:24.730
You bluff it to seem less of a freak.

01:26:24.850 --> 01:26:27.330
What drug dealer?

01:26:51.370 --> 01:26:54.210
- Hey, Lenny, how you doing?
- It's private back here.

01:26:54.450 --> 01:26:57.170
- It's OK, we know each other. Right, kid?
- How did you know I was in here?

01:26:57.410 --> 01:26:59.170
The Jag's out front.

01:26:59.410 --> 01:27:02.130
What are you still doing here, Lenny?
There's plenty of tattoo parlours up north.

01:27:02.370 --> 01:27:05.570
I guess I wanted to get something down
before it slipped my mind.

01:27:05.810 --> 01:27:07.530
- Give me the keys, I'll move it.
- It'll be all right.

01:27:07.770 --> 01:27:09.570
- Wait out there.
- Oh, for Christ...

01:27:09.810 --> 01:27:13.370
Give me a minute,
I've got to get something for you.

01:27:16.290 --> 01:27:21.210
<i>Fact six. Car licence SG13 7IU.</i>

01:27:25.770 --> 01:27:30.250
Look, wait a minute, will ya?

01:27:31.290 --> 01:27:33.330
- We gotta get you out of here.
- Why?

01:27:33.570 --> 01:27:36.250
Oh, man. Come on, Leonard.
How many times I gotta tell you?

01:27:36.490 --> 01:27:38.690
- It's not safe for you to hang around.
- Why not?

01:27:38.930 --> 01:27:41.970
Because that cop's looking for you.
I gotta get you a new identity...

01:27:42.210 --> 01:27:45.290
some new clothes, a different car would do for now. 
Put these on.

01:27:45.530 --> 01:27:47.170
Whoa, whoa. What cop?

01:27:47.410 --> 01:27:51.170
He's a bad cop. 
He's the one that checked you into the Discount Inn.

01:27:51.410 --> 01:27:55.010
He's been calling you for days, 
slipping envelopes under your door, shit like that.

01:27:55.250 --> 01:27:58.930
- How do you know this?
- He told me. He's been laughing at you.

01:27:59.170 --> 01:28:00.370
- You're full of shit.
- No, I'm not.

01:28:00.610 --> 01:28:02.410
He knows you're no good on the phone
so he's been calling you up.

01:28:02.650 --> 01:28:04.410
Sometimes you don't answer the phone...

01:28:04.650 --> 01:28:07.170
so he slips shit under your door
to scare you into answering it...

01:28:07.410 --> 01:28:12.210
giving you a line of crap about John G
being a local drug dealer. Jimmy Grants.

01:28:12.450 --> 01:28:14.970
- Who's Jimmy Grants?
- Leonard, Jimmy's the drug dealer.

01:28:15.210 --> 01:28:18.410
The cop wants to know how his operation is run. 
He's got some score in mind.

01:28:18.650 --> 01:28:20.930
- Somehow you're involved.
- How do you know him?

01:28:21.170 --> 01:28:26.490
I'm a snitch. He's a cop from out of town.
The local boys put us together.

01:28:26.730 --> 01:28:28.810
If he knew I was helping you,
he'd fucking kill me.

01:28:29.050 --> 01:28:32.530
So take these clothes, 
put them on and get the fuck out of here.

01:28:32.770 --> 01:28:36.090
Come on, Leonard, just go.

01:28:54.050 --> 01:28:57.410
You are full of shit.

01:28:58.610 --> 01:29:01.010
<i>Come by after. Natalie.</i>

01:29:01.250 --> 01:29:04.610
<i>Ferdy's bar.</i>

01:29:43.250 --> 01:29:46.890
Hey, Jimmy.

01:29:46.890 --> 01:29:50.010
I'm sorry, I, uh,
thought you were somebody else.

01:29:50.250 --> 01:29:51.850
Sorry.

01:29:52.090 --> 01:29:55.570
That's OK.

01:30:07.250 --> 01:30:11.250
This Jimmy Grants deals drugs out of the bar 
where his girlfriend works?

01:30:11.490 --> 01:30:14.890
But he's not going to bring her along?
He'll come by himself, right?

01:30:15.130 --> 01:30:18.850
I always figured the drugs angle
would be the best way to get him.

01:30:19.090 --> 01:30:22.210
No, officer. I'm as ready as I'll ever be.

01:30:22.450 --> 01:30:26.250
You're in the lobby?
What do you look like?

01:30:26.490 --> 01:30:28.930
I'll be right there.

01:31:08.770 --> 01:31:11.170
Lenny!

01:31:11.810 --> 01:31:15.290
Officer Gammell?

01:31:16.650 --> 01:31:20.130
Yeah. Come on.

01:31:34.690 --> 01:31:38.090
- Hey, smile.
- Oh, don't, uh... Not here.

01:31:38.330 --> 01:31:41.810
Over here.

01:31:44.610 --> 01:31:47.010
Is it Officer or Lieutenant Gammell?

01:31:47.250 --> 01:31:49.970
You know what?
Don't write Gammell, just Teddy.

01:31:50.210 --> 01:31:54.250
- Why?
- I'm undercover.

01:31:55.330 --> 01:31:57.810
This is the directions, where he's going.

01:31:58.050 --> 01:32:00.650
- My number's on the bottom if you...
- You're not coming?

01:32:00.890 --> 01:32:05.090
Nah, it wouldn't be appropriate.

01:32:07.370 --> 01:32:11.450
Nice picture. I look thin.

01:32:12.570 --> 01:32:15.170
Hey, Lenny!

01:32:15.410 --> 01:32:18.290
Make him beg.

01:33:36.010 --> 01:33:39.490
Teddy!

01:33:40.010 --> 01:33:42.650
Hey, Teddy!

01:33:44.050 --> 01:33:47.330
Teddy!

01:33:48.850 --> 01:33:50.810
Jimmy.

01:33:51.050 --> 01:33:54.010
- What the fuck are you doing here?
- You Jimmy Grants?

01:33:54.250 --> 01:33:56.010
Expecting any other Jimmys, memory man?

01:33:56.250 --> 01:34:00.170
- Do you remember me?
- Yeah, I remember you.

01:34:00.410 --> 01:34:02.570
Where the fuck's Teddy?

01:34:02.810 --> 01:34:05.370
Well?

01:34:07.370 --> 01:34:09.050
Motherfuck!

01:34:09.290 --> 01:34:11.610
What are you doing?

01:34:12.170 --> 01:34:13.170
Strip.

01:34:13.410 --> 01:34:17.290
- You're making a big fucking mistake!
- Strip!

01:34:17.290 --> 01:34:20.090
My associates are not the kind of people
you wanna piss off.

01:34:20.330 --> 01:34:21.770
Don't say anything else.

01:34:22.010 --> 01:34:26.410
- I knew I couldn't trust that fuck!
- Take it off.

01:34:29.970 --> 01:34:31.850
Your pants, too.

01:34:32.090 --> 01:34:34.290
- Why?
- I don't wanna get blood on them.

01:34:34.530 --> 01:34:38.210
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Wait, wait, wait!
Did he tell you what I was bringing?

01:34:38.450 --> 01:34:42.090
- Take your fuckin' pants off!
- I've got two hundred grand in the car!

01:34:42.330 --> 01:34:44.730
- Just take it!
- You think you can bargain with me?

01:34:44.970 --> 01:34:47.050
- Just take the money and walk away.
- I don't want your fucking money.

01:34:47.290 --> 01:34:49.450
Then, what?

01:34:49.690 --> 01:34:54.370
- What do you want from me?
- I want my fucking life back!

01:36:20.570 --> 01:36:23.250
Sammy.

01:36:28.250 --> 01:36:30.130
<i>He said Sammy.</i>
<i>How does he know about Sammy?</i>

01:36:30.370 --> 01:36:33.850
Oh, fuck.

01:36:51.370 --> 01:36:54.330
<i>What have I done?</i>

01:36:54.570 --> 01:36:55.570
Hey, mister! I need help!

01:36:55.810 --> 01:36:59.090
There's a guy in here, he's hurt bad.
We gotta get him to a doctor.

01:36:59.330 --> 01:37:01.410
All right.

01:37:01.650 --> 01:37:03.690
I don't know what happened.
I've got this memory thing.

01:37:03.930 --> 01:37:06.610
- Do I know you?
- No. Don't worry, I'm a cop.

01:37:06.850 --> 01:37:09.850
- Is he still breathing?
- Well, I don't know. Maybe.

01:37:10.090 --> 01:37:14.730
- What the hell were you guys doing?
- I don't remember, I have this condition.

01:37:14.970 --> 01:37:18.050
I hope it's not as serious as his
cos this guy's dead.

01:37:18.290 --> 01:37:21.850
- Ow! Lenny! That shit kills!
- So you remember me now, huh?

01:37:22.090 --> 01:37:26.370
- You are a fucking cop!
- And I'm the guy that helped you find him.

01:37:26.610 --> 01:37:32.450
- Get up! Get up!
- Lenny, you got the wrong idea!

01:37:33.690 --> 01:37:35.530
Who is that? He knew me.

01:37:35.770 --> 01:37:38.170
Of course he did, he raped your wife,
he fucked up your brain.

01:37:38.410 --> 01:37:40.210
Bullshit! He's not the guy.

01:37:40.450 --> 01:37:44.010
His name is James F Grants. John G.
Check your tattoos.

01:37:44.250 --> 01:37:48.370
- Why did he bring two hundred grand?
- What?

01:37:48.770 --> 01:37:50.810
- What was it for?
- Amphetamines I told him I had.

01:37:51.050 --> 01:37:54.330
- Is this a drug deal?
- No. Yeah, that and your thing.

01:37:54.570 --> 01:37:57.770
Look, Jimmy's your guy. 
I figured we'd make a few dollars on the side.

01:37:58.010 --> 01:38:00.610
- How did he know me?
- The Discount Inn.

01:38:00.850 --> 01:38:04.890
He dealt out of there. The guy at the front desk 
let him know if anybody came round.

01:38:05.130 --> 01:38:07.170
He called Jimmy
the minute he saw you taking a picture.

01:38:07.410 --> 01:38:09.570
- You're fucking using me.
- No! You get half.

01:38:09.810 --> 01:38:12.050
He knew about Sammy,
why would I tell him about Sammy?!

01:38:12.290 --> 01:38:15.370
You tell everybody about Sammy!
Everybody who'll listen!

01:38:15.610 --> 01:38:17.490
"Remember Sammy Jankis?"
"Remember Sammy Jankis?"

01:38:17.730 --> 01:38:20.530
Great story.
Gets better every time you tell it.

01:38:20.770 --> 01:38:24.370
So you lie to yourself to be happy.
There's nothing wrong with that.

01:38:24.610 --> 01:38:29.410
We all do it. Who cares if there's a few little details 
you'd rather not remember?

01:38:29.650 --> 01:38:32.850
- What the fuck are you talking about?
- I don't know.

01:38:33.090 --> 01:38:37.570
Your wife surviving the assault.
Her not believing your condition.

01:38:37.810 --> 01:38:42.610
The torment and pain and anguish
tearing her up inside.

01:38:42.850 --> 01:38:45.090
The insulin.

01:38:45.330 --> 01:38:47.770
That's Sammy, not me.
I told you about Sammy.

01:38:48.010 --> 01:38:50.730
Yeah, right.
Like you tell yourself over and over again.

01:38:50.970 --> 01:38:54.170
Condtitioning yourself to remember,
learning through repetition.

01:38:54.410 --> 01:38:56.970
Sammy let his wife kill herself.
Sammy ended up in an institution.

01:38:57.210 --> 01:39:00.210
Sammy was a con man. A faker.

01:39:00.450 --> 01:39:02.370
I never said that Sammy was faking.

01:39:02.610 --> 01:39:05.210
You exposed him for what he was.
A fraud.

01:39:05.450 --> 01:39:08.290
I was wrong. That's the whole point.

01:39:08.530 --> 01:39:13.170
- See, Sammy's wife came to me...
- Sammy didn't have a wife.

01:39:14.250 --> 01:39:18.530
It was your wife who had diabetes.

01:39:22.650 --> 01:39:25.130
Ouch!

01:39:25.650 --> 01:39:28.210
My wife wasn't diabetic.

01:39:28.450 --> 01:39:31.930
You sure?

01:39:34.650 --> 01:39:36.370
Ouch! Cut it out!

01:39:36.610 --> 01:39:38.410
She wasn't diabetic.

01:39:38.650 --> 01:39:42.090
You think I don't know my own wife?
What the fuck is wrong with you?

01:39:42.330 --> 01:39:45.090
I guess I can only make you remember 
the things you want to be true.

01:39:45.330 --> 01:39:47.810
- Like old Jimmy down there.
- He's not the right guy.

01:39:48.050 --> 01:39:49.970
He was to you.

01:39:50.210 --> 01:39:53.290
Come on, you got your revenge.
Enjoy it while you still remember.

01:39:53.530 --> 01:39:55.810
What difference does it make
whether he was your guy or not?

01:39:56.050 --> 01:39:57.930
- It makes all the difference.
- Why? You're never gonna know.

01:39:58.170 --> 01:39:59.730
- Yes, I will.
- No, you won't.

01:39:59.970 --> 01:40:02.130
- Somehow I'll know.
- You won't remember!

01:40:02.370 --> 01:40:03.610
When it's done, I will know.

01:40:03.850 --> 01:40:08.330
I thought so, too, I was sure of it,
but you didn't!

01:40:10.330 --> 01:40:14.930
That's right. The real John G.
I helped you find him over a year ago.

01:40:15.170 --> 01:40:17.770
- He's already dead.
- Don't lie to me any more.

01:40:18.010 --> 01:40:19.850
Look, Lenny...

01:40:20.090 --> 01:40:23.010
I was the cop assigned to your wife's case, 
I believed you.

01:40:23.250 --> 01:40:25.490
I thought you deserved a chance for revenge.

01:40:25.730 --> 01:40:28.810
I'm the one that helped you find the other guy 
in your bathroom that night.

01:40:29.050 --> 01:40:31.050
The guy that cracked your skull
and fucked your wife.

01:40:31.290 --> 01:40:35.130
We found him, you killed him.

01:40:35.250 --> 01:40:37.370
But you didn't remember.

01:40:37.610 --> 01:40:42.410
So I helped you start looking again,
looking for the guy you already killed.

01:40:42.650 --> 01:40:47.010
- Oh, yeah? So who was he?
- Just some guy. Does it matter who?

01:40:47.250 --> 01:40:51.650
No reason, Lenny, no conspiracy,
just bad fucking luck.

01:40:51.890 --> 01:40:56.770
Couple of junkies too strung out
to realise your wife didn't live alone.

01:40:56.970 --> 01:41:01.410
But when you killed him
I was so convinced that you'd remember.

01:41:01.650 --> 01:41:03.890
But it didn't stick.

01:41:04.130 --> 01:41:07.770
Like nothing ever sticks,
like this won't stick.

01:41:10.330 --> 01:41:12.290
I took that picture.

01:41:12.530 --> 01:41:16.010
Just when you did it.

01:41:17.130 --> 01:41:21.770
Look how happy you are.
I wanted to see that face again.

01:41:22.010 --> 01:41:24.250
- Oh, gee, thanks!
- Fuck you.

01:41:24.490 --> 01:41:28.210
I gave you a reason to live
and you were more than happy to help.

01:41:28.450 --> 01:41:34.450
You don't want the truth. 
You make up your own truth, like your police file.

01:41:34.690 --> 01:41:37.490
It was complete when I gave it to you.
Who took out the twelve pages?

01:41:37.730 --> 01:41:38.890
You, probably.

01:41:39.130 --> 01:41:41.290
- No, it wasn't me, see, it was you.
- Why would I do that?

01:41:41.530 --> 01:41:44.090
To create a puzzle you could never solve.

01:41:44.330 --> 01:41:46.090
Do you know how many towns...

01:41:46.330 --> 01:41:50.210
how many John Gs or James Gs?
I mean, shit, Lenny, I'm a fucking John G.

01:41:50.450 --> 01:41:53.370
- Your name's Teddy.
- My mother calls me Teddy.

01:41:53.610 --> 01:41:55.410
My name's John Edward Gammell.

01:41:55.650 --> 01:42:01.730
Cheer up. 
There's plenty of John Gs for us to find.

01:42:03.570 --> 01:42:07.610
All you do is moan! 
I'm the one that has to live with what you've done.

01:42:07.850 --> 01:42:09.650
I'm the one that put it all together.

01:42:09.890 --> 01:42:14.210
You, you wander around, you're playing detective. 
You're living a dream, kid.

01:42:14.450 --> 01:42:17.170
A dead wife to pine for,
a sense of purpose to your life...

01:42:17.410 --> 01:42:22.650
a romantic quest that you wouldn't end
even if I wasn't in the picture.

01:42:22.890 --> 01:42:25.770
- I should kill you.
- Quit it! Lenny, come on.

01:42:26.010 --> 01:42:30.410
You're not a killer.
That's why you're so good at it.

01:42:30.930 --> 01:42:32.730
Come on, what are you doing?

01:42:32.970 --> 01:42:38.530
You know what time it is?
It's beer o'clock, I'm buying.

01:42:38.690 --> 01:42:42.170
Fuck!

01:42:49.690 --> 01:42:51.770
<i>I'm not a killer.</i>

01:42:52.010 --> 01:42:56.850
<i>I'm just someone who wanted to make things right.</i>

01:42:59.450 --> 01:43:04.770
<i>Can I just let myself forget</i>
<i>what you've told me?</i>

01:43:19.050 --> 01:43:22.530
<i>Can I just let myself forget</i>
<i>what you made me do?</i>

01:43:35.970 --> 01:43:40.330
<i>You think I just want another puzzle to solve?</i>
<i>Another John G to look for?</i>

01:43:40.570 --> 01:43:44.290
<i>You're a John G.</i>

01:43:45.130 --> 01:43:48.650
<i>So you can be my John G.</i>

01:43:55.130 --> 01:43:57.730
<i>Do I lie to myself to be happy?</i>

01:43:57.970 --> 01:44:00.770
<i>In your case, Teddy...</i>

01:44:01.290 --> 01:44:04.770
<i>yes, I will.</i>

01:44:15.290 --> 01:44:17.090
Hey! Hey, that's not your car!

01:44:17.330 --> 01:44:20.130
- It is now.
- Jesus Christ, you can't take it!

01:44:20.370 --> 01:44:22.450
- Why not?
- Because the guy you just killed owns it!

01:44:22.690 --> 01:44:26.010
Somebody'll recognise it.

01:44:26.250 --> 01:44:29.930
You know, I think I'd rather be mistaken 
for a dead guy than a killer.

01:44:30.170 --> 01:44:33.130
I might hang on to this for a while.

01:44:33.370 --> 01:44:35.010
Lenny.

01:44:35.250 --> 01:44:38.530
Look, don't...
Will you help me find the keys?

01:44:38.770 --> 01:44:40.570
Help me find my keys!

01:44:40.810 --> 01:44:43.130
Lenny!

01:44:47.730 --> 01:44:50.090
Lenny!

01:45:02.090 --> 01:45:05.210
<i>I have to believe in a world</i>
<i>outside my own mind.</i>

01:45:05.450 --> 01:45:07.250
<i>I have to believe</i>
<i>that my actions still have meaning.</i>

01:45:07.490 --> 01:45:10.770
<i>Even if I can't remember them.</i>

01:45:11.010 --> 01:45:17.010
<i>I have to believe that when my eyes are closed,</i>
<i>the world's still here.</i>

01:45:17.250 --> 01:45:21.050
<i>Do I believe the world's still here?</i>

01:45:22.370 --> 01:45:25.370
<i>Is it still out there?</i>

01:45:26.850 --> 01:45:30.050
<i>Yeah.</i>

01:45:30.810 --> 01:45:34.970
<i>We all need memories</i>
<i>to remind ourselves who we are.</i>

01:45:35.730 --> 01:45:38.890
<i>I'm no different.</i>

01:45:49.410 --> 01:45:52.570
<i>Now, where was I?</i>

01:45:59.850 --> 01:46:04.330
<i>We lay in each other's arms</i>

01:46:05.330 --> 01:46:08.970
<i>But the room is just an empty space</i>

01:46:09.210 --> 01:46:12.570
<i>I guess we lived it out</i>

01:46:12.810 --> 01:46:15.890
<i>Something in the air</i>

01:46:16.130 --> 01:46:17.490
<i>We smile too fast</i>

01:46:17.730 --> 01:46:22.610
<i>Then can't think of a thing to say</i>

01:46:22.970 --> 01:46:27.010
<i>Lived with the best times</i>

01:46:28.010 --> 01:46:31.490
<i>Left with the worst</i>

01:46:32.850 --> 01:46:37.930
<i>I've danced with you too long</i>

01:46:38.930 --> 01:46:41.410
<i>Nothing left to save</i>

01:46:41.650 --> 01:46:47.010
<i>There's something in the air</i>

01:46:47.250 --> 01:46:50.850
<i>Something in my eye</i>

01:46:51.090 --> 01:46:55.970
<i>I've danced with you too long</i>

01:46:56.210 --> 01:46:58.370
<i>Yeah</i>

01:46:58.610 --> 01:47:02.690
<i>Something in the air</i>

01:47:02.930 --> 01:47:08.490
<i>Something in my eye</i>

01:47:18.610 --> 01:47:20.610
<i>Abracadoo</i>

01:47:20.850 --> 01:47:24.330
<i>I lose you</i>

01:47:24.370 --> 01:47:26.930
<i>We can't avoid the clash</i>

01:47:27.170 --> 01:47:30.650
<i>The big mistake</i>

01:47:31.010 --> 01:47:34.730
<i>Now we're gonna pay and pay</i>

01:47:35.250 --> 01:47:41.570
<i>I guess you know</i>
<i>I never wanted anyone more than you</i>

01:47:41.810 --> 01:47:46.050
<i>Lived all our best times</i>

01:47:47.010 --> 01:47:51.010
<i>Left with the worst</i>

01:47:51.890 --> 01:47:56.850
<i>I've danced with you too long</i>

01:47:57.850 --> 01:48:00.210
<i>Say what you will</i>

01:48:00.450 --> 01:48:07.330
<i>But there's something in the air</i>

